4AD is a British independent record label formed in 1979 (and still active today) best known for the Pixies (who released their debut EP and next two albums on the label) and The Breeders (who have released all their albums with the label)


The compilation 1980 Forward was released in 2005, celebrating 25 years of releasing music

According to 4AD&amp;#039;s official website, the CD is out of stock (which really means it&amp;#039;s out of print, after all, they&amp;#039;re the people who released it), although you can download it for Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â£7.99, it&amp;#039;s unavailable in the USA and Canada

Although the website lists the catalogue number as CAD 2525 CD, meaning it was a full-length EP released on CD, and the 25th release in their 25th year, the case actually says TAD 2525 CD, TAD meaning it was a temporary release


Anyway, that&amp;#039;s enough of the history lesson, now on to the reason you&amp;#039;re here - you were searching for one of the bands on the compilation and found this by mistake, but now you&amp;#039;re here it looks kind of interesting, so why not try it out?

